Apparently it's been over a decade since avant jazz deity Pharoah Sanders recorded any new music, it took Sam Shephard aka Floating Points to coax the 80 year old out of near-retirement.

label: Warp Records
description:
Recorded when she was just 22, Nala Sinephro's debut album casts a potent spell, animating her harp, guitar and modular synth compositions with sturdy rhythms and horns. It's jazz that exists very much in the present, as much related to Rune Grammofon and ECM's surreal minimalism as Alice Coltrane's devotional bliss. V good!

Nick León's Future Times debut slots into the label's club library like a quarter in a pinball table. Time-distorted hard-swung grooves that stir León's customary polyrhythms into house and techno architectures that point directly at the stars.
